                  our understanding of how to interpret them in strong
                  magnetic fields is still rather limited. Recent
                  results from flush-mounted Langmuir probes in divertor
                  plates are used to highlight the problem areas, in
                  particular non-saturation of the ion current and low
                  electron to ion saturation current ratios. The
                  importance of measuring the parallel flow velocity in
                  the plasma edge is highlighted and recent developments
