   global confinement with the edge pressure gradient is found which is
   connected with a loss of the favourable density dependence predicted by
   the 1TER-92P and ITER-93H ELMy H-mode scalings. At high density, better
   confinement is achieved in H-modes with an edge pressure gradient below
   the ideal ballooning limit, e.g. during type III ELMy H-mode with
